# Agent Instructions

## Validation

- `make lint` — run often during development
- `make check` — run before considering work done
- `make quality` — run before marking work complete
- Prefer `nix develop path:. --command make check` so required tools come from `flake.nix`

## Code Conventions

- Reference `src/seed/` for file organization patterns
- Prefer stdlib; consider established libraries for complex problems
- Every function that can fail must raise a typed exception
- No dead code — if it is not called, delete it
- Aim for high branch coverage

## Testing

- Every source file needs a test file
- Test error paths, not just happy paths
- Tests must contain real assertions
- Use names like `test_should_do_x_when_y`
- Mock at boundaries, not internal helpers

## What Lint Catches Automatically

Do not worry about these — lint will catch them:
- File organization
- File/function length limits
- Placeholder comments
- `print()` statements
- Import ordering and formatting
